	<meta name="description" content="I wanted to share with you how quick and easy the frosting technique is that I used on my Red Velvet Strawberry Shortcake. I have only ever used this method on whipped cream (as in Cool Whip) so at this point I can only recommend it for that type of frosting. Here is all I did! Apply a thick layer of whipped cream. This works better when it is chilled. Well. I should start out by saying a did a rough crumb coat in vanilla frosting. Not whipped cream. Just in case some of the cake wanted to peek through..." />
